Pricing
Glasswire is committed to respecting your privacy. This Website Privacy Policy explains the ways
                        in which Glasswire, a brand owned by Domotz Inc, and its subsidiaries and affiliates
                        (collectively, ”Domotz”, “Glasswire”, “we”, “our”, or “us”) collect,
                        use, and disclose information about you through our websites including Glasswire.com and
                        Glasswire.com sub-domains (the “Site”).
This Website Privacy Policy was last updated in October 2021. We may change it from time to
                        time, so please check back regularly to keep informed of any updates.
Data collection
You may create an account with Glasswire to receive marketing communications, join our forum or
                        post on our blogs.
Information You Provide:
We collect, and associate with your account, any information that
                        you provide Glasswire when you use the Site, such as when you create an account, purchase a
                        product, or contact us. Information you provide us can include, but is not limited to, (a) your
                        name, email address, physical address, username, password, and other registration information;
                        (b) transaction-related information, such as billing and shipping addresses, and any other
                        information necessary to complete the transaction; (c) and information you provide when you
                        contact us.
We do not collect or store your credit card information. Our credit card processing service
                        provider will collect and store full payment card information from you.
Usage:
We collect information from and about the devices you use to access the Site. This
                        includes things like IP addresses, the type of browser and device you use, the web page you
                        visited before coming to the Site, and identifiers associated with your devices.
Cookies and other technologies:
We use cookies, web beacons and other tracking
                        technologies (“Cookies”) to provide, improve, protect and promote our services, as explained in
                        the Cookies Policy section below.
Third Party Sites and Social Media Features:
Our Site contains links to other websites
                        operated by third parties, such as social media companies Youtube and Twitter. These third party
                        sites may collect information about you if you click on a link and they may record information
                        about your browsing behaviour. Your interaction with these features is governed by the privacy
                        policy of the company providing them. We do not control what information these third parties
                        collect. Please review their privacy policies and your privacy settings on your social media
                        sites and think carefully before clicking on third party links.
We do not currently respond to web browser “do not track” signals or other mechanisms that
                        provide a method to opt out of the collection of information across the networks of websites and
                        online services in which we participate. If we do so in the future, we will describe how we do
                        so in this Website Privacy Policy. Visit
allaboutdnt.org
for more information.
Data Use
We may use the information we collect to provide, improve and protect our services, such as
                        for:
Delivering marketing communications about Glasswire-related services, products or
                            promotions. We may use service providers to send these messages on our behalf, but we do not
                            share your email address with any other third parties without your permission.
Providing you with products, services, or information you request, for example when you
                            contact us for remote support and troubleshooting;
Providing you with information about the Site or required notices;
Customizing your experience when using the Site;
Improving the Site and services that we provide, such as by better tailoring our content to
                            your needs and preferences;
Generating and analyzing statistics about your use of the Site;
Detecting, preventing, and responding to fraud, intellectual property infringement,
                            violations of law, or other misuse of the Site.
We may also combine or aggregate any of the information collected through the Site or elsewhere
                        for any of these purposes.
Data Sharing
We do not share personal information for any commercial or marketing purpose unrelated to the
                        delivery of Glasswire products and services without asking you first. We do not rent or sell our
                        customer lists.
The following are the limited situations where we may share personal information:
Trusted Partners working for Glasswire:
Glasswire may occasionally use certain third party
                        service providers to help us provide, improve, protect, and promote our services. These third
                        parties may access your information only to perform tasks on our behalf and in compliance with
                        this Website Privacy Policy.
Other users:
Certain features on the Site may allow you to share information with other
                        users, such as your name, email address and additional information. Please take care if you
                        choose to do so, as we do not control how these other users will handle your information.
Business Transitions:
If we are involved in a merger, acquisition or sale of all or a
                        portion of our assets, your information may be transferred as part of that deal. We will use
                        reasonable efforts to try to ensure that the purchaser uses your personal information in a
                        manner that is consistent with this Website Privacy Policy.
Law & Order:
We may disclose your information to third parties if we determine that such
                        disclosure is reasonably necessary to (a) comply with the law; (b) protect any person from death
                        or serious bodily injury; (c) prevent fraud or abuse of Glasswire or our users; or (d) protect
                        Glasswire’s property rights.
We may share some aggregated, anonymized and non-personal information publicly and with our
                        partners. For example, we may publish trends about internet speed, or statistics about the type
                        of electronic devices installed in the homes of our customers. This information may also be
                        shared with other users to help them understand their network as compared to others in the
                        Glasswire community, raise awareness about technical issues or help us generally improve our
                        system. We take steps to ensure this non-personal information is not being associated with any
                        specific user and we require our partners to do the same.
Cookie Policy
We use cookies, web beacons and other tracking technologies (referred to collectively throughout
                        this policy as “Cookies”) to provide, improve, protect and promote our services. Cookies help us
                        with things like remembering your username for your next visit, and allow us to collect
                        information about your browsing behaviour when you use our Site, including for example, browser
                        type, IP address, domains, page views, referring/exit pages, and information about how you
                        interact with our web pages. In some of our email messages, we use a “click-through URL” linked
                        to content on the Site. We may track this click-through data to help us measure the
                        effectiveness of our customer communications.
Our site uses first party cookies (i.e. cookies set directly by us to your device) as well as
                        cookies served by third parties for the purposes outlined below. Some of the Cookies the Site
                        uses only remain on your device while your browser is open (these cookies are known as “session
                        cookies”) while others remain for longer periods (these are known as “permanent cookies”). The
                        Site uses the following Cookies:
Google Ads Cookies
Google Tag Manager Cookies
Google Analytics Cookies
Google Display and remarketing Cookies
Facebook Advertising cookies
You have the right to choose whether or not to accept Cookies. However, they are an important
                        part of how our Site works, so you should be aware that if you choose to refuse or remove
                        cookies, this could affect the availability and functionality of the site.
Most web browsers are set to accept cookies by default. If you prefer, you can usually choose to
                        set your browser to remove or reject browser cookies. To do so, please follow the instructions
                        provided by your browser which are usually located within the “Help,” “Tools” or “Edit”
                        facility. Some third parties also provide the ability to refuse their cookies directly by
                        clicking on an opt-out link, and we have indicated where this is possible in the table
                        above.
Further information about cookies, including how to see what cookies have been set on your device
                        and how to manage and delete them, is available at the following URLs:
www.allaboutcookies.org
and
www.youronlinechoices.eu
.
GlassWire Cookie Policy. We use cookies to personalise content and ads, to provide social media features and to analyse our traffic. We also share information about your use of our site with our social media, advertising and analytics partners who may combine it with other information that you’ve provided to them or that they’ve collected from your use of their services.
Cookies are small text files that can be used by websites to make a user's experience more efficient.
The law states that we can store cookies on your device if they are strictly necessary for the operation of this site. For all other types of cookies we need your permission.
This site uses different types of cookies. Some cookies are placed by third party services that appear on our pages.
You can at any time change or withdraw your consent from the Cookie Declaration on our website.
Learn more about who we are, how you can contact us and how we process personal data in our Privacy Policy.
Please state your consent ID and date when you contact us regarding your consent.
