Data security & retention
Security:
We take security seriously and care about the integrity of your personal information.
                        We use administrative, physical, and technical safeguards to protect the confidentiality of
                        personally identifiable information, including encryption, firewalls and SSL (Secure Sockets
                        Layer).
Retention:
We will retain your information for as long as your account is active, as needed to
                        provide you services or as necessary to comply with our legal obligations, resolve disputes, or
                        to enforce our agreements.
Where:
To provide you with our services, we may store, process and transmit information in
                        locations around the world – including those outside your country. Those countries may not
                        provide the same level of protection for your personal information as your home country, and may
                        be available to the governments or agencies under a lawful order of those countries. Where this
                        is the case, we will use reasonable efforts to try to ensure that your personal information is
                        protected in accordance with this Website Privacy Policy. By using the Site, you consent to such
                        transfer to, and processing in, these countries. Information may also be stored locally on the
                        devices you use to access the services.
Children
This Site is not directed to, nor do we knowingly collect information from, children under the
                        age of 16. If you become aware that a child under your care has provided us with information
                        without your consent, please contact us at the contact information below.
Your Choice
If you no longer wish to receive non-transactional communications from us, please click the
                        “unsubscribe” link in any email from us, update your marketing preferences in your account, or
                        contact us at the address below.
To make a request to have personal information maintained by us returned to you, amended or
                        removed, please email
privacy@glasswire.com
. Requests to access, change, or remove your
                        information will be handled within thirty (30) days.
Updates to this Policy
We may revise this Website Privacy Policy, from time to time, and will post the most current
                        version on our website. Please check back frequently to see any updates or changes to this
                        Website Privacy Policy. If a revision materially changes your rights, we will notify you and
                        provide you with the opportunity to consent to such changes before applying them to that
                        information.
Contact
If your contact information changes, if you no longer wish to receive marketing communications
                        from us, if you wish to inquire about information we have collected about you, or if you have
                        questions or concerns about Glasswire privacy, please contact us at
privacy@glasswire.com
.
